The paper discusses the use of digital communication signals through tissue for potential biomedical applications, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound). The paper also mentions achieving high data rates, which could indicate that it belongs to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the possibility of inbody ultrasonic communications with implanted medical devices, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.BI (Bioinformatics). Finally, the paper mentions the transmission of real-time video-rate data, which could indicate that it belongs to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
